    • SubscriptionResponseDto

      public SubscriptionResponseDto(Long id, Optional<LocalDate> startDate, Optional<LocalDate> endDate, boolean terminated, boolean suspended, String contentIdentifier, Long subscriberId, boolean active, boolean canBeSuspended, boolean canBeTerminated, boolean canBeUnsuspended)
      Constructs a new SubscriptionResponseDto using the supplied arguments.
      Parameters:
      id - the subscription identifier
      startDate - the subscription start date
      endDate - the subscription end date
      terminated - true if the subscription has been terminated
      suspended - true if the subscription is suspended
      contentIdentifier - a string that describes the content that is the subject of the subscription
      subscriberId - the identifier of the subscriber that is the beneficiary of this subscription
      active - true if this subscription is active
      canBeSuspended - true if the subscription can be suspended
      canBeTerminated - true if the subscription can be terminated
      canBeUnsuspended - true if the subscription can be unsuspended
